C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20my%20actual%20name%20until%20recently.%20I'd%20see%20the%20name%20Jane%20Walker%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20mail%20or%20hear%20it%20called%20out%20in%20a%20doctor's%20office%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20a%20name%20I%20identified%20with.%20I%20finally%20changed%20it%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20surreal%20to%20finally%20see%20my%20legal%20name%20match%20my%20identity%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20to%20have%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-kids-names-to-include-my-last-name-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elast%20name%20match%20my%20children%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20husband.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acdfe95b-b59c-4def-8466-99859b9e90ce%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20didn't%20think%20I%20needed%20to%20change%20my%20name%20until%20I%20had%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElliott%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-maiden-name-middle-names-family-legacy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20middle%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20I'd%20been%20using%20it%20as%20my%20preferred%20first%20name%20for%20nearly%2020%20years%2C%20which%20is%20longer%20than%20I'd%20used%20my%20given%20first%20name%2C%20Jane.%20I%20started%20using%20Harrell%20as%20my%20last%20name%20socially%20when%20I%20got%20married%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20didn't%20make%20the%20change%20official.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20changing%20my%20name%20had%20less%20to%20do%20with%20feeling%20like%20I'd%20built%20an%20incredible%20brand%20at%20work%20with%20my%20maiden%20name%20and%20more%20to%20do%20with%20dreading%20the%20mountain%20of%20paperwork%20that%20comes%20with%20changing%20a%20name.%20I'd%20heard%20it%20wasn't%20necessarily%20a%20difficult%20task%2C%20per%20se%2C%20but%20definitely%20a%20tedious%20and%20annoying%20one%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20convinced%20it%20was%20worth%20it%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20very%20important%20to%20me%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-last-name-husband-hyphenated-maiden-married-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etake%20my%20husband's%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20to%20have%20a%20shared%20family%20name%20when%20we%20had%20our%20children.%20Initially%2C%20I%20thought%20I'd%20use%20Elliott%20Harrell%20socially%20and%20my%20given%20legal%20name%20when%20mandated%20and%20that%20everything%20would%20be%20fine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20figured%20I%20could%20put%20up%20with%20the%20annoyance%20of%20being%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bwrong%26quot%3B%20name%20at%20appointments%20and%20the%20vexing%20but%20humorous%20exercise%20of%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20combination%20of%20names%20I%20had%20used%20to%20order%20take%20out%20with%20(was%20it%20Jane%20Walker%2C%20Elliott%20Walker%2C%20or%20Elliott%20Harrell%3F)%20if%20it%20would%20mean%20escaping%20an%20overly%20bureaucratic%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fine%20for%20a%20while%2C%20even%20after%20our%20first%20daughter%20was%20born.%20I%20didn't%20love%20that%20we%20had%20different%20last%20names%2C%20but%20I%20also%20didn't%20feel%20a%20compelling%20push%20to%20do%20the%20work%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhated-first-name-wanted-to-change-worried-insult-parents-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Echange%20my%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20changed%20with%20our%20second%20daughter's%20arrival.%20She%20surprised%20us%20six%20weeks%20early%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20have%20a%20name%20picked%20out.%20In%20the%20NICU%2C%20the%20nurses