.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fsolothurn-jacqueline-zund-nicolas-steiner-akka-1236008669%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Low-income%20Americans%20wait%20years%20to%20get%20housing%20vouchers%20that%20are%20often%20impossible%20to%20use.%20Fixing%20the%20system%20could%20mean%20more%20funding%20and%20less%20red%20tape.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apartment%20buildings%20on%20Orchard%20Street%20in%20the%20Lower%20East%20Side%20neighborhood%20of%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6646424814fb5b23cc5d489d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApartment%20buildings%20on%20Orchard%20Street%20in%20the%20Lower%20East%20Side%20neighborhood%20of%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Housing%20Choice%20Voucher%20Program%20is%20the%20biggest%2C%20most%20effective%20federal%20housing%20assistance%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20housing%20vouchers%20are%20both%20severely%20underfunded%20and%20complicated%20to%20use.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProposals%20include%20increasing%20funding%2C%20easing%20inspection%20rules%2C%20and%20exploring%20cash%20assistance%20options.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbpp.org%2Fblog%2Fmaking-rental-assistance-work-better-for-people-struggling-to-afford-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20effective%20housing%20assistance%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%20is%20facing%20a%20slew%20of%20mounting%20challenges.%20The%20federal%20Housing%20Choice%20Voucher%20Program%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Section%208%2C%20is%20also%20the%20biggest%2C%20aiding%20about%205%20million%20people%20in%202.3%20million%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fpdredge%2Fpdr-edge-featd-article-051623.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclining%20number%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20landlords%20across%20the%20US%20are%20accepting%20the%20vouchers%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20recipients%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fpublications%2Fpdf%2Fsec8success.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efailing%20to%20secure%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoucher%20holders%20pay%20about%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20toward%20rent%2C%20while%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%20covers%20the%20rest%20%E2%80%94%20up%20to%20what%20it%20determines%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hud.gov%2Fprogram_offices%2Fpublic_indian_housing%2Fprograms%2Fhcv%2Flandlord%2Ffmr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efair%20market%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20lots%20of%20research%20showing%20the%20program%20is%20very%20effective%20at%20reducing%20homelessness%20and%20dangerous%20housing%20conditions%20like%20overcrowding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20gives%20low-income%20people%20more%20power%20to%20choose%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20building%2C%20and%20unit%20they%20want%20to%20live%20in%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20to%20stay%20there.%20Kids%20whose%20families%20have%20vouchers%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20bounce%20from%20school%20to%20school%20or%20end%20up%20in%20foster%20care%2C%20said%20Will%20Fischer%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20housing%20policy%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20on%20Budget%20and%20Policy%20Priorities%20(CBPP).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e6a0caf-0ae2-4cdc-af08-afcb0eed6d20%5C%22%3EVouchers%20aren't%20helping%20as%20much%20as%20they%20should%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20program%20is%20only%20reaching%20a%20fraction%20of%20those%20who%20could%20benefit%20from%20it.%20Only%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbpp.org%2Fresearch%2Fhousing%2Fpolicy-basics-project-based-vouchers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOnly%25201%2520in%25204%2520families%2Cof%2520families%2520eligible%2520for%2520vouchers.%26amp%3Btext%3DAgencies%2520can%2520maintain%2520separate%2520waitlists%2Csingle%2520waitlist%2520for%2520all%2520vouchers.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20in%20four%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20eligible%20for%20a%20voucher%20get%20one%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20average%20wait%20time%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbpp.org%2Fresearch%2Fhousing%2Ffamilies-wait-years-for-housing-vouchers-due-to-inadequate-funding%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20and%20a%20half%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20about%2010%20million%20additional%20low-income%20households%20are%20going%20without%20the%20help%20they%20qualify%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20someone%20gets%20a%20voucher%2C%20it%20can%20be%20very%20challenging%20to%20find%20a%20home%20that%20meets%20the%20program's%20requirements%2C%20and%20a%20landlord%20willing%20to%20accept%20the%20applicant%20within%20the%20period%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20as%20short%20as%2060%20days%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0allotted%20to%20find%20a%20unit.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20landlords%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20(76%25)%2C%20Fort%20Worth%20(78%25)%2C%20and%20Philadelphia%20(67%25)%20refused%20to%20rent%20to%20voucher%20holders%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Fresearch%2Fpublication%2Fpilot-study-landlord-acceptance-housing-choice-vouchers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202018%20study%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20it's%20illegal%20in%20some%20places%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecity.nyc%2F2023%2F10%2F18%2Frenters-guide-voucher-income-discrimination-apartments%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscriminate%20against%20voucher%20holders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20practice%20isn't%20outlawed%20everywhere.%20Some%20places%2C%20including%20Iowa%2C%20have%20banned%20protections%20for%20voucher%20holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F05%2F25%2Fnyregion%2Fny-vouchers-homeless-discrimination.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20property%20owners%20and%20brokers%20have%20accused%20them%20of%20explicitly%20denying%20applicants%20based%20on%20their%20source%20of%20income.%20Racial%20discrimination%20against%20voucher%20holders%2C%20who%20are%20disproportionately%20Black%2C%20is%20also%20rampant%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstateline.org%2F2021%2F05%2F12%2Fbiden-wants-to-offer-more-housing-vouchers-many-landlords-wont-accept-them%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvocates%20say%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20many%20landlords%20say%20the%20administrative%20process%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20includes%20an%20inspection%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-03%2FReforming_the_Inspections_Process.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20slow%20or%20burdensome%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20only%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fportal%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpdf%2FVoucher-Success_Rates.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%25%20of%20voucher%20recipients%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20successful%20in%20finding%20a%20home%20with%20the%20subsidy.%20Those%20lucky%20enough%20to%20get%20a%20voucher%20and%20move%20into%20an%20apartment%20sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F04%2F05%2Fnyregion%2Fny-housing-voucher-program-problems.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGetting%2520a%2520voucher%2520in%2520the%2C%252C%2520while%2520illegal%252C%2520is%2520widespread.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eface%20issues%20with%20their%20city%20and%20state%20housing%20authorities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20are%20wrongly%20ejected%20from%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268025fbf-3db7-477c-9f4a-491a807cfbb3%5C%22%3EMore%20funding%20could%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20single%20biggest%20challenge%20the%20program%20faces%20is%20that%20it's%20severely%20underfunded.%20Government%20housing%20assistance%20for%20the%20poorest%20renters%20has%20dropped%20to%20the%20lowest%20levels%20in%2025%20years%20even%20as%20the%20number%20who%20need%20the%20aid%20has%20soared%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20Harvard%20housing%20experts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F19%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fhousing-aid-rent-costs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20in%20December%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFully%20funding%20housing%20vouchers%20would%20mean%20many%20more%20housing-insecure%20and%20unhoused%20people%20would%20get%20help.%20It's%20up%20to%20Congress%20to%20make%20this%20change%2C%20as%20it%20determines%20how%20much%20the%20federal%20government%20spends%20on%20its%20housing%20assistance%20programs%2C%20mainly%20Housing%20Choice%20Vouchers%20and%20public%20housing%2C%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20budget%20for%20fiscal%20year%202025%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20requested%20a%20%242.5%20billion%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fomb%2Fbriefing-room%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Ffact-sheet-the-presidents-budget-cuts-housing-costs-boosts-supply-and-expands-access-to-affordable-housing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20for%20voucher%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%202023%20levels.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20funding%20increase%2C%20vouchers%20would%20be%20guaranteed%20to%20very%20low-income%20veterans%20and%20youth%20aging%20out%20of%20foster%20care%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0two%20groups%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20homelessness.%20But%20Republicans%20have%20sought%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-in-debt-ceiling-bill-republicans-cut-housing-aid-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20HUD%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20challenging%20to%20significantly%20expand%20the%20reach%20of%20vouchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenny%20Schuetz%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20urban%20economics%20and%20housing%20policy%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20Congress%20could%20consider%20reducing%20the%20amount%20of%20voucher%20funding%20per%20household%20so%20that%20it%20can%20offer%20vouchers%20to%20more%20households.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20gonna%20have%20an%20honest%20conversation%20about%20how%20much%20Congress%20is%20willing%20to%20fund%2C%20then%20the%20number%20of%20people%20could%20be%20higher%20than%20it%20is%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20isn't%20interested%20in%20spreading%20funding%20more%20thinly%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Frent-cost-us-2024-housing-national%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erents%20spike%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country.%20Instead%2C%20it%20boosted%20funding%20per%20voucher%20by%20increasing%20its%20limits%20for%20fair%20market%20rents%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hud.gov%2Fpress%2Fpress_releases_media_advisories%2Fhud_no_23_186%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetter%20keep%20up%20with%20rent%20increases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allowed%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnlihc.org%2Fresource%2Frepublican-house-appropriators-block-nonprofits-receiving-grants-huds-economic-development%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%2C000%20additional%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20use%20vouchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20Long%20Island%20City%20and%20Manhattan%20from%20rooftop%2C%20Greenpoint%2C%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634de5d10dfcda409665934%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22915%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20apartment%20buildings%20in%20Long%20Island%20City%2C%20Queens.%3Cp%3ELindsey%20Nicholson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c983d420-bd4e-4e6d-9d73-4f05ffcd7eee%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Graffiti%20can't%20harm%20you'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second-biggest%20problem%2C%20experts%20say%2C%20is%20the%20home%20inspection%20process.%20Before%20a%20voucher%20recipient%20can%20sign%20a%20lease%20on%20a%20home%2C%20it%20must%20be%20inspected%20by%20the%20local%20housing%20authority%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20meets%20a%20slew%20of%20health%20and%20safety%20standards.%20But%20that%20process%20can%20create%20lengthy%20delays%2C%20cause%20landlords%20to%20keep%20a%20unit%20empty%20and%20miss%20out%20on%20rent%20payments%2C%20and%20ultimately%20result%20in%20the%20voucher%20holder%20losing%20out%20on%20the%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERising%20rent%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20impact%20that%20has%20on%20households%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20a%20much%20bigger%20concern%20than%20unsafe%20housing%2C%20a%20recent%20in-depth%20report%20on%20HUD's%20housing%20quality%20standards%20and%20inspection%20processes%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-03%2FReforming_the_Inspections_Process.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUrban%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20author%20of%20the%20report%2C%20Michael%20Stegman%2C%20called%20inspecting%20every%20apartment%20before%20a%20voucher%20holder%20can%20move%20in%20%26quot%3Bakin%20to%20using%20a%20bazooka%20to%20kill%20a%20gnat%26quot%3B%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DxZZ-0DyrKHY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20panel%20discussion%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Urban%20Institute%20report%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStegman%20detailed%20how%20the%20quality%20of%20rental%20housing%20across%20the%20country%20has%20dramatically%20improved%20since%20Section%208%20was%20first%20implemented%20in%20the%20mid-1970s.%20And%20he%20recommended%20that%20HUD%20try%20out%20different%20inspection%20regimes%2C%20including%20allowing%20landlords%20and%20tenants%20to%20self-certify%20that%20the%20home%20meets%20health%20and%20safety%20guidelines%2C%20with%20unannounced%20inspection%20audits%20by%20local%20housing%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20has%20made%20some%20efforts%20to%20address%20the%20issue%2C%20including%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coons.senate.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fbipartisan-bill-seeks-to-expand-housing-choice-and-opportunity-for-low-income-families-in-rental-assistance-program%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebipartisan%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20designed%20to%20incentivize%20landlords%20and%20loosen%20inspection%20requirements.%20Housing%20authorities%20across%20the%20country%20have%20been%20more%20successful%20in%20streamlining%20their%20inspection%20processes%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20made%20some%20headway%20on%20the%20issue.%20Last%20October%2C%20slightly%20less%20burdensome%20regulations%2C%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hud.gov%2Fprogram_offices%2Fpublic_indian_housing%2Freac%2Fnspire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENSPIRE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20went%20into%20effect.%20The%20new%20process%20attempts%20to%20zero%20in%20on%20health%20and%20safety%20issues%20while%20relaxing%20regulations%20around%20non-threatening%20conditions%2C%20like%20traffic%20noise%20and%20graffiti.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGraffiti%20can't%20harm%20you%2C%20can't%20kill%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Tara%20Radosevich%2C%20an%20assessment%20manager%20at%20HUD%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20might%20be%20something%20you%20may%20not%20want%20to%20live%20near%2C%20but%20if%20it%20doesn't%20harm%20a%20resident%2C%20we're%20willing%20to%20accept%20that%20our%20units%20may%20be%20in%20areas%20with%20graffiti.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20experts%20say%20much%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20reduce%20administrative%20burdens%20and%20boost%20landlord%20participation.%20One%20solution%20is%20to%20offer%20so-called%20holding%20fees%2C%20which%20would%20pay%20landlords%20while%20they%20hold%20a%20unit%20vacant%20during%20the%20inspection%20process%2C%20Fischer%20said.%20Another%20way%20to%20incentivize%20property%20owners%20is%20to%20create%20a%20fund%20to%20reimburse%20landlords%20for%20damage%20to%20units%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregon.gov%2Fohcs%2Ffor-providers%2FDocuments%2Ffactsheets%2FFACTSHEET-HCLGP.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOregon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtoncountyor.gov%2Fhousing%2Fregional-long-term-rent-assistance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%3C%2Fa%3E%20State%20have%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20fixes%2C%20Fischer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbpp.org%2Fblog%2Fmaking-rental-assistance-work-better-for-people-struggling-to-afford-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20written%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20include%20allowing%20voucher%20funding%20to%20be%20used%20for%20security%20deposits%20and%20other%20upfront%20costs%2C%20offering%20voucher%20holders%20help%20in%20the%20home%20search%20process%20and%20giving%20them%20more%20time%20to%20secure%20a%20home%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20voucher%20recipients%20to%20move%2C%20and%20banning%20discrimination%20against%20voucher%20holders%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20also%20exploring%20offering%20housing%20assistance%20in%20cash.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fpdredge%2Fpdr-edge-frm-asst-sec-090523.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20piloting%20a%20direct%20cash%20transfer%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20rent%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20housing%20vouchers.%20Cash%20payments%20for%20housing%2C%20researchers%20say%2C%20have%20a%20slew%20of%20benefits%2C%20and%20cut%20the%20red%20tape%20associated%20with%20vouchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiving%20people%20money%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20advantages%