ing%20in%20May%202024.%20A%20study%20suggests%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20push%20back%20Russian%20lines%20with%2014%20more%20fully%20equipped%20brigades.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20can%20go%20back%20on%20the%20offensive%2C%20but%20it%20will%20require%20more%20troops%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20RAND%20expert%C2%A0believes%20Ukraine%20can%20build%20a%20strike%20force%20capable%20of%20a%20decisive%20offensive.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERight%20now%2C%20Ukraine's%20biggest%20problem%20isn't%20lack%20of%20manpower%2C%20but%20lack%20of%20equipment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%2014%20to%2021%20well-equipped%20brigades%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20eject%20Russian%20forces%20from%20all%20Ukrainian%20territory%2C%20according%20to%20an%20American%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%20whether%20Ukraine%20can%20find%20the%20manpower%2C%20and%20whether%20Ukraine's%20allies%20are%20willing%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20to%20arm%20them%20properly.%20Yet%20what%20is%20remarkable%20is%20that%20despite%20Ukraine%20being%20outnumbered%20and%20outgunned%20by%20Russia%2C%20Kyiv%20still%20has%20a%20genuine%20chance%20of%20winning%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20has%20really%20kind%20of%20disturbed%20me%20is%20that%20we're%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20into%20this%20war%2C%20and%20no%20one's%20put%20forth%20a%20potential%20theory%20of%20victory%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Bohnert%2C%20a%20defense%20analyst%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corp.%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20data%20from%20a%20variety%20of%20sources%2C%20Bohnert%20has%20calculated%20the%20financial%20costs%20of%20Ukrainian%20victory%2C%20or%20at%20least%20for%20munitions.%20Ukraine's%20Western%20allies%20like%20the%20US%20and%20members%20of%20the%20EU%20would%20have%20to%20spend%20%2454%20billion%20to%20%2472%20billion%20per%20year%20to%20manufacture%20enough%20missiles%20and%20artillery%20shells%20to%20enable%20Ukraine%20to%20go%20on%20the%20offensive%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20potential%20formula%20for%20Ukrainian%20victory%2C%20there%20are%20two%20prerequisites.%20One%20is%20Ukraine%20amassing%20a%20sufficiently%20powerful%20ground%20combat%20force%20that%20can%20defeat%20the%20estimated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Frussian-military-objectives-and-capacity-ukraine-through-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E500%2C000%20Russian%20troops%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Ukraine.%20Past%20history%20isn't%20promising.%20An%20ill-prepared%20Ukrainian%20counteroffensive%20in%20summer%202023%20sputtered%20amid%20Russian%20minefields%20and%20inexperienced%20Ukrainian%20troops%20struggling%20to%20master%20newly%20arrived%20Western%20combat%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Bohnert%20points%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRR1320.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2015%20RAND%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20US%20Army%20that%20suggests%20Ukraine%20could%20recapture%20its%20territory.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20study%2C%20researchers%20analyzed%20how%20big%20a%20force%20NATO%20would%20need%20to%20dislodge%20a%20Russian%20force%20that%20had%20invaded%20the%20Baltic%20States%2C%20and%20was%20entrenched%20on%20Balkan%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20that%20an%20additional%2014%20brigades%20and%20their%20accompanying%20enablers%20will%20be%20needed%2C%20with%20perhaps%20six%20brigades%20and%2086%2C000%20total%20soldiers%20coming%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20eight%20brigades%20and%20a%20similar%20number%20of%20troops%20from%20U.S.%20NATO%20allies%2C%20along%20with%20supporting%20air%20and%20sea%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20the%202015%20study%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Russian%20forces%20solidly%20dug%20in%20behind%20minefields%20and%20fortifications%20across%20eastern%20and%20southern%20Ukraine%2C%20that%20Baltic%20scenario%20bears%20similarities%20to%20the%20situation%20that%20Ukraine%20faces%20today.%20Or%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bclose%20enough%20for%20ROM%20%5Brough%20order%20of%20magnitude%5D%20estimation%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20amassing%2021%20brigades%20of%20roughly%204%2C000%20soldiers%20each%20%E2%80%94%20and%20training%20and%20equipping%20them%20to%20NATO%20standards%20%E2%80%94%20won't%20be%20easy.%20For%20now%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20struggling%20to%20contain%20Russian%20offensives%20that%20have%20achieved%20small%20but%20symbolic%20gains%20in%20the%20north%20and%20south%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20put%20this%20in%20perspective%2C%2021%20brigades%20is%20something%20like%2050%20to%2060%20percent%20of%20the%20active-duty%20US%20Army%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%20%26quot%3BOr%2C%20basically%20you%20would%20have%20to%20take%20the%20equivalent%20of%20the%20UK%2C%20German%20or%20French%20armies%2C%20train%20them%20and%20give%20them%20100%20percent%20of%20all%20the%20kit%20they%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukr%20military%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644a092f27898f532d7bf61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20fire%20D-30%20artillery%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Chasiv%20Yar%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20May%2012%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20fears%20that%20Ukraine%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-exploiting-ukraine-manpower-shortage-thin-line-breakthrough-war-expert-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erunning%20out%20of%20manpower%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20spurred%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-advances-bill-for-prisoners-to-serve-in-military-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20allow%20prison%20inmates%20to%20be%20conscripted%20%E2%80%94%20Bohnert%20believes%20Ukraine%20can%20find%20the%20personnel%20for%20a%20strike%20force%20capable%20of%20launching%20a%20decisive%20offensive.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20were%20to%20rotate%20forces%20over%20about%20a%20two-year%20time%20frame%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20new%20conscription%20they're%20pushing%2C%20they%20probably%20could%20get%20enough%20brigades%20converted%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20Ukraine's%20biggest%20problem%20isn't%20lack%20of%20manpower%2C%20but%20lack%20of%20equipment.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20their%20battalions%20are%20still%20not%20fully%20equipped%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bohnert.%20%26quot%3BNATO%20needs%20to%20give%20what%20they've%20promised%20and%20be%20willing%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20all%20their%20existing%20forces%20get%20supplied%20to%20at%20least%20some%20minimal%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20up%20the%20other%20vital%20question%3A%20How%20many%20munitions%20does%20Ukraine%20need%3F%20While%20tanks%20and%20drones%20have%20been%20useful%20in%20the%20war%2C%20the%20most%20devastating%20weapons%20have%20been%20artillery%20and%20long-range%20guided%20rockets.%20However%2C%20these%20weapons%20devour%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20howitzer%20shells%20or%20scarce%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20sending%20in%2025%2C000%20to%2030%2C000%20new%20troops%20per%20month%2C%20according%20to%20Bohnert.%20Which%20means%20that%20Ukraine%20must%20inflict%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20casualties%20per%20month%20%E2%80%94%20or%20about%201%2C000%20casualties%20per%20day%20%E2%80%94%20to%20erode%20Russian%20strength.%20In%202024%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20inflicting%20800%20to%201%2C000%20casualties%20per%20day%2C%20despite%20being%20%26quot%3Bmunition-starved%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%20Given%20sufficient%20quantities%20of%20munitions%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20inflict%20enough%20losses%20to%20decisively%20attrit%20Russian%20forces%20that%20have%20already%20sustained%20an%20estimated%20500%2C000%20casualties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20demand%20for%20munitions%20also%20depends%20on%20what%20kind%20of%20war%20Ukraine%20chooses%20to%20wage.%20Bohnert%20estimated%20munitions%20costs%20for%20two%20scenarios%3A%20one%20where%20Ukraine%20remains%20on%20the%20defensive%2C%20and%20the%20other%20where%20it%20goes%20on%20the%20offensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20with%20a%202023%20Estonian%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkaitseministeerium.ee%2Fen%2Fsetting-transatlantic-defence-success-military-strategy-ukraines-victory-and-russias-defeat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplan%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20laid%20out%20a%20roadmap%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20defeat%20Russia.%20%26quot%3BThis%20war%20can%20be%20won%20within%20the%20next%20three%20years%20or%20less%2C%20by%20adjusting%20and%20increasing%20the%20Euro-Atlantic%20community's%20military%20production%20output%20and%20assistance%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20imposing%20the%20perspective%20of%20an%20intolerable%20level%20of%20attrition%20on%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Estonians%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Estonians%20estimated%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20need%20a%20constant%20stream%20of%20munitions.%20This%20includes%202.4%20million%20artillery%20shells%2C%204%2C800%20air%20defense%20missiles%20capable%20of%20protecting%20cities%20from%20Russian%20missiles%2C%20and%208%2C760%20guided%20bombardment%20rockets%20per%20year.%20Even%20this%20doesn't%20cover%20all%20the%20items%20Ukraine%20would%20need%2C%20such%20as%20air%20defense%20weapons%20for%20the%20front-line%20troops%2C%20Bohnert%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20factored%20in%20data%20on%20combat%20operations%20and%20munitions%20usage%20from%20RAND%20studies%20dating%20back%20to%20the%201990s%2C%20which%20examined%20conflicts%20such%20as%20Desert%20Storm.%20Overall%2C%20Bohnert%20estimated%20that%20%2420%20billion%20to%20%2435%20billion%20per%20year%20would%20be%20needed%20if%20Ukraine%20merely%20stays%20on%20the%20defensive%2C%20and%20%2454%20billion%20to%20%2472%20billion%20per%20year%20if%20it%20goes%20on%20the%20offensive.%20And%20still%20these%20figures%20are%20incomplete.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20including%20training%2C%20sustainment%20or%20equipment%2C%20which%20easily%20could%20be%2050%25%20or%20double%20that%20price%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bohnert.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20but%20actually%20about%20the%20same%20that%20the%20US%20spent%20on%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20for%2015%20years%20straight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20depletion%20of%20Western%20stockpiles%20and%20struggles%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20to%20boost%20arms%20production%2C%20Bohnert%20believes%20that%20NATO%20can%20meet%20Ukraine's%20needs.%20The%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20aims%20to%20produce%2014%2C000%20GMLRS%20rockets%20in%202025%2C%20and%20it%20can%20produce%20up%20to%20700%20cruise%20missiles%20per%20year.%20America%20and%20NATO%20together%20manufacture%20about%204%2C600%20anti-aircraft%20missiles%20per%20year.%20And%20what%20Ukraine's%20allies%20can't%20manufacture%20themselves%2C%20they%20might%20be%20able%20to%20acquire%20from%20other%20nations%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20this%20is%20impossible%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20feasible.%20It's%20just%20going%20to%20take%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmple%20Ukrainian%20ammunition%20stockpiles%20would%20partly%20alleviate%20Ukraine's%20manpower%20crunch.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20basically%20substituting%20metal%20for%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20will%20have%20to%20be%20a%20pretty%20big%20increase%20in%20Western%20donations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInevitably%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20divergence%20between%20what%20Ukraine%20needs%20and%20what%20it%20will%20get.%20For%20example%2C%20US%20arms%20production%20may%20be%20diverted%20to%20the%20Pacific%20to%20face%20China%2C%20other%20American%20allies%20such%20as%20Israel%20also%20need%20weapons%2C%20and%20the%20US%20and%20European%20public%20may%20balk%20at%20the%20price%20tag.%20It's%20also%20unrealistic%20to%20expect%20that%20Russia%20will%20passively%20await%20a%20Ukrainian%20buildup.%20The%20recent%20appointment%20of%20economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fruble-bullet-vladimir-putin-put-economist-andrei-belousov-charge-military-sergei-shoigu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrei%20Belousov%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20minister%20of%20defense%20suggests%20that%20Putin%20intends%20to%20mobilize%20his%20nation's%20resources%20for%20a%20long%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20it%20is%20revealing%20that%20despite%20being%20outnumbered%20and%20outgunned%20by%20Russia%2C%20there%20remains%20serious%20belief%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20win%20a%20military%20victory.%20The%20question%20is%20how%20to%20accomplish%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETwitter%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmipeck%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-can-still-beat-russia-comes-down-to-western-aid-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716022802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2